From: Abhishek Vyas <abhishek.vyas@inventum.net>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] cmd_upgrade: keep operational certs across firmware upgrade

The keep_redirector firmware upgrade (uCentral app) preserves the birth
certs but not the operational cert/CA, so the AP loses its operational
certificate across an upgrade. Add operational.pem and operational.ca to
the keep list; they are only archived when present (fs.stat guard).

Signed-off-by: abhishek vyas <abhishek.vyas@inventum.net>
---
--- a/command/cmd_upgrade.uc
+++ b/command/cmd_upgrade.uc
@@ -55,6 +55,7 @@
 		"/etc/ucentral/cas.pem", "/etc/ucentral/cert.pem",
 		"/etc/ucentral/redirector.json", "/etc/ucentral/dev-id",
 		"/etc/ucentral/key.pem", "/etc/config/ucentral",
+		"/etc/ucentral/operational.pem", "/etc/ucentral/operational.ca",
 		"/etc/ucentral/profile.json", "/etc/ucentral/restrictions.json"
 ];
 for (let f in files)
